parameters: Indeed! I've never been here before.
'In the toughest situations, two heads are better than one.'
I don't know what its medicinal properties are,
but perhaps it is full of vitality.
And if I'm not wrong, our last herb is over there...
No way I can make it that far.
Aww... So close yet so far.
We should have chosen a different path instead.
Without you, I wouldn't have made it this far.
but it looks like someone already took it.
Seems like you two could use a little help, hmm?
And if I'm not wrong, again... our last herb is over there...
No way I can make it that far.
Aww... So close yet so far.
Why is it always on the other cliff...?
We've come this far together, and that's what matters.
Perhaps this wasn't the day for that herb.
But look, an unexpected ally approaches.
Yes, we're trying to reach that herb up on the cliff,
but we can't quite reach it.
I just so happen to be an expert at flying!
assistance from a fairy like me doesn't come for free.
and if you can solve it, I'll assist you.
Whatever answer you choose, you have to explain it in detail!
(You cheeky little ass, I'll get you next time...)
Looks like you're having trouble with the herb on the other cliff again?
Yes, for some reason, it's always on the other cliff.
You've got to make it worth my while for my assistance.
I'm tall when I'm young and short when I'm old.
It starts out tall when it's new and gets shorter as it burns.
Flowers start as buds and bloom into tall stems with petals.
However, they wither uh- Not while right...
Balloons are inflated when they're new,
I'm full of holes but still hold water.
Oh crap! They don't hold water...
Colanders have many holes but are used to drain water from food,
It has holes in it but can still absorb and hold water.
Phew, thinking is not my strong suit...
the more you leave behind. What am I?
The answer was in the question all along!
What has a head, a tail, is brown, and has no legs?
Well, they're brown, have heads and tails,
but oh... they do have legs, don't they?
It fits all the clues perfectly.
and you could say the ends are its 'head' and 'tail,' but no, that doesn't quite work...
I speak without a mouth and hear without ears.
I have no body, but I come alive with the wind.
but it's just a sound bouncing back.
It 'comes alive' and dances in the wind,
It makes sounds with the wind,
kind of like it's talking and listening, right?
Phew, thinking is not my strong suit...
What can travel around the world while staying in a corner?
What comes once in a minute, twice in a moment, but never in a thousand years?
It happens many times a minute and in every moment, but you wouldn't count it over years in the same way.
It appears once in 'minute' and twice in 'moment' but not at all in 'a thousand years'.
You blink at least once a minute,
maybe twice in a moment of surprise, but it's not something you'd measure in years.
I am not alive, but I grow;
I don't have lungs, but I need air;
I don't have a mouth, but water kills me. What am I?
Well, they grow and need air,
but too much water can drown them,
though they do need some water to live.
It 'grows' as air fills it, but a splash of water can pop it.
It grows, needs air to burn, but water extinguishes it.
Phew, thinking is not my strong suit...
What has keys but can't open locks,
and you can enter but can't go outside?
Has keys, a space bar, and an 'Enter' key,
but it can't unlock anything or take you outside.
So, you need to go outside sometime and touch grass.
You've solved all three riddles, my clever friends.
As promised, I shall retrieve the final herb for you.
We're right on the edge of the cliff!!!
It's urgent, we need to get the last herb!
